HEADWORD: myxobacterium
<hw>myxobacterium</hw> <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>myxobacteria</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <def>A type of bacteria that
form colonies in self-produced slime; they inhabit moist soils or
decaying plant matter or animal waste.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> myxobacterium, myxobacter, gliding bacteria, slime
bacteria.</syn>⟦br⟧
